Description: Sailor Moon fights for justice in the name of the Moon and the mysterious Moon Princess. Along the way, she recruits other girls to be Sailor Scouts) and join her fight against evil.
Title: SAILOR MOON, VOL. 2
Author: Naoko Takeuchi

Description: This is a manga adaptation of the best selling children’s series about ordinary housecats trying to fulfill extraordinary destinies.
Title: WARRIORS: BEYOND THE CODE, VOL. 2
Author: Erin Hunter

Description: Following in the footsteps of Sailor Moon, 13-year-old Minako Aino transforms into Sailor V. to protect the earth.
Title: CODENAME: SAILOR, VOL. 2
Author: Naoko Takeuchi

Description: Negi, the boy wizard, learns he will be teaching English at an all-girls high school in Japan, but he must keep his powers a secret.
Title: NEGIMA! MAGISTER NEGI MAGI, VOL. 32
Author: Ken Akamatsu

Description: The SOS Brigade is a school club dedicated to meeting time travelers or aliens or anyone fantastic. In this volume, April Fool’s Day is here.
Title: THE MELANCHOLY OF SUZUMIYA HARUHI-CHAN, VOL. 4
Author: Nagaru Tanigawa

Description: A gaggle of female ninjas plot to bring Raizo, the illegitimate son of a ruling family, to power.
Title: NINJA GIRLS, VOL. 8
Author: Hosana Tanaka

Description:
The Pokemon saga continues with the introduction of two new trainers: Black and White.
OMAMORI HIMARI
Title: POKEMON BLACK AND WHITE, VOL. 4
Author: Hidenori Kusaka

Description: Himari is a cat-spirit sworn to protect teenage Yuuto. In this volume: Himari must cope with a shrunken form.
Title: OMAMORI HIMARI, VOL. 5
Author: Milan Matra

Description: The SOS Brigade is a school club dedicated to meeting time travelers or aliens or anyone fantastic. Their main mission: keep Haruhi happy because she has the power to destroy the universe (but doesn’t know it).
Title: THE MELANCHOLY OF HARUHI SUZUMIYA, VOL. 10
Author: Nagaru Tanigawa

Description: Misao Harada can see into a magical realm where she is the bride demon of prophecy.
Title: BLACK BIRD, VOL. 11
Author: Kanoko Sakurakoji
